text: Quintus Volusius Saturninus (born AD 25As inferred from the fact his father was born in 38/37 BC, and sired Saturninus at the age of 63. (Pliny the Elder, Natural History, VII.62)) was a senator in the Roman Empire. He served with Publius Cornelius Scipio and was made consul in 56.Tacitus, Annales xiii.25 ==References== Category:25 births
title: Quintus Volusius Saturninus
